Welcome to Filtrator for fastq file!
It is simple script to filter reads from your fastq files by several parameters:
* minimal length
* GC content
and save passed and unpassed reads (if you need it) to separated files.


To run filtrator execute filter_fastq_modified.py from command line with nesessary arguments:
'python3 filter_fastq_modified.py <arguments> <fastq_file>'

Arguments:
'--min_length' <int> - specify the min len of reads;
'--keep_filtered' - use it if you want to write unpassed reads to file;
'--gc_bounds' <min GC-content> [optional]<max GC-content> - specify min GC-content of reads or the interval from min to max GC content
'--output_base_name' <name> - set the name for output file(s); the filename(s) will be like '<name>__passed.fastq' (and '<name>__failed.fastq').


P.S. Sorry for my english!



